cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DB, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the problem of missing data in a large database of plant traits, and proposes a new method for trait prediction that leverages the hierarchical phylogenetic structure of the plant kingdom. This problem is closely related to the field of machine learning, specifically matrix completion and factorization, which suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for incorporating hierarchical structure, which could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.DB (Databases).
